deck: Explorer/archeologist.
description:
Origin

Archeological partner to Dick Kane, the men search for the Earth for lost treasures.

Creation

Drawn by Howard Larsen.

Major Story Arcs

While on an expedition in the jungles of the Middle East, Dick and Ted encounter a massive storm. They find refuge in a cave but are soon beset by an earthquake that opens the ground and swallows them. Underground, they find a mound of ice. Inside that ice is a beautiful woman, perfectly preserved. Dick has the brilliant idea of digging her out. Doing so causes her to awaken. She claims to be Princess Tais and leads them further into the cave to help her people win a war. The air becomes thicker and chokes the men. They finally find the princess's home in ruins. They take her to the surface where the air is lighter and they can breathe again. Unfortunately, this air reduces the princess to dust. The men go home.
name: Ted Briggs

deck: A pirate.
description:

Sailor of the high seas, this pirate plunders where he can.

Besetting a ship from Ormuz, the pirates jump aboard expecting a huge plunder. This particular pirate eyes Malu and desires her. He engages Garth in combat and nearly gets the upper hand by tripping the soldier with a whip. But, as all foes before him, the pirate falls to Garth.
name: Pirate of Abmur

deck: Runner of the Manoch slave market.
description:
Origin

Runner of the Manoch slave market.

Creation

Drawn by Howard Larsen.

Major Story Arcs

Manoch is supposedly hired by Phao to come before the King of Ormuz to lie about owning Malu. He claims she was his slave and just recently sold to Garth, the very man trying to pass Malu off as the king's lost daughter. Despite this all being a lie, the king sides with Phao and, based on Manoch's testimony, banishes Malu and Garth from his kingdom.
name: Manoch

Irina is a devout Christian, even after the Kokabiel incident and learning that God is dead, she still remain with the Church and serves as Arch Angel Michale's peerage with the rank of Ace of Spades.
description:
Irina Shidou is a young woman who appeared with Xenovia, tasked by the Church to retrieve the missing Excalibur s. It is revieled that she is Issei's childhood friend, though he confused her for a boy then.

Irina is a devout Christian, even after the Kokabiel incident and learning that God is dead, she still remain with the Church and serves as Arch Angel Michale's peerage with the rank of Ace of Spades.

Appearance

Irina Shidou is Hyoudou Issei's childhood friend so one could say that they are the same age. She has long light brown hair reaching down to thigh which is tied at both side (Twin-tails held with a blue scrunchy). Her eyes are colored violet.

She wears the standard tight fitting Church battle outfit, after transferring to Kuoh Academy and staying at Hyoudou Issei's house, she starts to wear the Kuoh Academy uniform with the addition of white sneakers with blue accents and black tights under her skirt.

After she was turned into an angle as part of Arch Angel Michael peerage, the letter "A" is printed in her right hand symbolizing her rank as "Ace".

Personality

Irina have a cheery and upbeat personality. She looks at everything in a positive manner to a fault. She is also a very devout christian. As a follower of her faith, she is inflexible and harsh to those who she thinks are against her faith. This is shown as the way she treated Asia after converting into a devil, the same could be expressed when Xenovia, her former partner also changed sides.

After she learned that God is dead, she shift her faith to Arch Angel Michael as he is the one who continued God's original work.

Power and Abilities

Agent of the Church

Irina, like Xenovia is a wielder of one of the Seven Excaliburs, Excalibur Mimic. This Excalibur can change into different shapes as the user desires making it a very versatile weapon. However, her weapon was stolen by Freed Sellzen upon her defeat at the order of the Fallen Angel General Kokabiel and was fused along with three stolen Excaliburs by Valper Galilei.

Angel

After Irina was converted into an angel, she gains the ability to project light based weapons such as a sword and a bow. She was also given a prototype of the Holy Demonic Sword based on the weapon used by Yuuto Kiba. Later, she was able to infused the sword with elemental attributes such as fire and ice.

Publisher: Kadokawa Games

Release Date: November 2013

Platform: Nintendo 3DS

Retail Price: $ 63.00

Overview:

- The main objective of the game is to build up Lust and perform moves such as Dress Break.

The story centers around Hyoudou Issei, a dim-witted, lecherous second-year high school student who was killed Raynare on his first date . Issei (Yuuki Kaji) is reincarnated as a devil, and from that day forward, he serves as an underling of Rias Gremory (Yōko Hikasa), a high-level devil who is also the prettiest girl of Kuoh Academy as part of her peerage.

The game has a unique system, the player advances by following his desires. The game's story parts reenact the anime's plot, particularly, Issei's daily school life surrounded by girls. The player engages in conversations with the heroines and improves (or ruins) his standing among them by making choices. According to Famitsu, "the key to winning is 'lust'!"

In each chapter of the game, there are also battles with various opponents. The battles have a typical turn-based system in which the player selects commands. The player can use the "lust power" accumulated in the story parts to increase the "Dress Break" damage against opponents in battle.

Light Novel

High School DxD is a light novel written by Ichiei Ishibumi and illustrated by Miyama-Zero and published by Fujimi Shobo. It is a Supernatural (Dealing with the topic of Gods, Devils, Etc.) action anime which the story centers on Hyoudou Issei, a perverted high school student who is nearly killed by his first date, Yuuma Amano, who is later revealed as the Fallen Angel Raynare. He is soon saved by Rias Gremory, a crimson-haired beauty who reveals herself as a Devil and part of the Gremory Clan. He finds himself reborn as a Devil with the purpose of serving her.

The story focuses on the ongoing battle between the the Three Super Natural Faction:

  • Devils
  • Fallen Angels
  • Angels

deck: Friend of New Warrior Slapstick.
description:
Origin

Michael Peterson is the best friend of Steve Harmon. Kidnapped by the clowns from Dimension X, he was saved by Steve. Recognizing his friend, he realized that Steve had just had an origin and helped him think of superhero name, Slapstick.

Later, while working on a school project, Mike and Steve go to the Museum of National History in Manhattan. However, their visit was interrupted by Doctor Yesterday, who wanted to use the museum to focus his powers. When the rest of the New Warriors show up he brings to life a skeleton of a Tyrannosaurus Rex and summons several warriors from the past to aid him. While his super-powered friends took on the time-displaced threats, Mike tried to find a way to help, but was captured. Mike was freed when Doctor Yesterday set things right again.

Other Media

Television

Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.

A reoccurring character and MCU Deathlok played by J. August Richards in Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.

Not much is known about Peterson's early life. Except that he was injured in a work related accident causing him to lose his job and his wife to leave him, leaving him to raise his son, Ace, alone. During his rehabilitation he was approached by Raina, a Centipede recruiter, offering treatment that could restore his health and put him back to work. Peterson agreed and was fitted with a Centipede device, which utilized alien metal, gamma radiation, the Extremis Virus, and the Super-Soldier Serum granting him super-strength and durability.

When the Centipede lab was destroyed by the detonation of another patient due to the instability of Extremis, Peterson saved a scientist from the burning building. His heroics were recorded by Skye, a member of the Rising Tide, and posted online, giving Peterson unwanted fame. The video also attracted the attention of S.H.I.E.L.D., who sent agents to investigate. Skye managed to track him down and warn him against S.H.I.E.L.D. Soon after, Peterson's condition began to deteriorate, both mentally and physically. Hoping to regain his old position Peterson visited his former workplace, but when he is rejected, attacked his old manager hospitalizing him. He then visited the Centipede scientist in the hospital, who convinced him that he needed to disappear, as the people behind Centipede did not want to be exposed. Convinced that he needed to try and rebuild his life, he took his son and broke into Skye's van, ordering her to take him to the nearest train station. He soon discovered that Skye was working with S.H.I.E.L.D., and escaped into the station; where he was confronted by by Agent Phil Coulson who tried to talk him down, before being shot by Agent Grant Ward with a tranquilizer and taken into S.H.I.E.L.D. custody. Ace is taken to live with Mike's sister.

After his recovery Mike is recruited into S.H.I.E.L.D., and although doctors had been unable to remove the Centipede device, the tranquilizer had somehow stabilized the Extremis. When Edison Po, a Centipede agent, was broken out of prison, Agent Coulson asked for him to be temporarily assigned to his team. During his time with the team there were some hostile feelings, mainly from Agents Ward and May, but after helping the team against Centipede agents in an abandoned warehouse he earned their trust. Afterward Michael told Coulson his thoughts about joining S.H.I.E.L.D full time, afraid to return to his son after he had seen his outrage at the train station. Coulson assured him his son would think no different of him and told him to think on his decision. Mike called his son to tell him he be returning. However after the encounter in Oakland Centipede learned that Mike was working with S.H.I.E.L.D. and abducted his son threatening to kill him if Peterson did not trade Coulson for Ace. With no other option Mike tricked the team into thinking that Centipede wanted him in exchange for his son. After getting his son to safety Mike attempted to redeem himself by going back to rescue Coulson only for Centipede to blow up the Bridge explode, apparently killing him.

It is later revealed that Mike had survived the blast, and been recovered by Centipede agents. He is badly burned and missing his right leg; a monitoring ocular implant replacing his right eye. Mike is later seen in a hyperbaric chamber in the possession of Ian Quinn, an associate of Centipede. After receiving a shipment from Cybertech, Quinn awakens Mike and equips him with a cybernetic leg labeled Project Deathlok. Mike is then ordered through his eye to eliminate the Cybertech team that had delivered the limb. When Coulson's team arrives at the facility Mike is ordered not to engage and leaves Quinn to his fate. Afterwards, Peterson covertly visits a playground and requests to see his son to which the Clairvoyant responds "Not yet".

Now calling himself Deathlok, Peterson is next seen attacking agents John Garrett and Triplett, who are getting close to The Clairvoyant. The two manage to repel Deathlok's attacks causing him to flee. Peterson is next sent to a nursing home where he confronts agents May and Blake. He critically injuring Blake, but May manages to tag him with a tracker before he leaves.The team tracks Deathlok to a race track and briefly encounter him again, but he retreats into the sewers.

After HYDRA's return and John Garrett's reveal as the Clairvoyant, Deathlok was sent to monitor Grant Ward, a double agent on Coulson's team, as he tried to get Skye to decrypt a hard drive containing all the information Coulson and his team had collected. When Skye tips off the police and escapes, Peterson appears and captures her. Returning to the Bus, Ward again attempts to coerce Skye to decrypt the hard drive. When he failed, Garrett ordered Deathlok to hurry up the operation, using one of the weapons in his armor he causes Ward to have a heart attack, giving Skye an ultimatum: decrypt the hard drive, or Ward dies. After try to reason with him and failing she relented, and Deathlok stopped Ward's heart attack. Later, when Coulson snuck aboard the plane to rescue Skye, Deathlok tried to prevent their escape, but failed when Coulson flew out the plane's cargo ramp with his flying car Lola. Ward starts to pursue, but Mike informs him Garrett had recalled them to the base in Cuba.

Some time after Mike is sent to Columbia where he assassinates a drug lord as a demonstration of Project Deathlok's effectiveness. Later, back on the Bus Peterson asked Raina her motives for working with Garrett, as he only did so out of fear for his life and that of his son, to which she responded that she wanted to help special people achieve their potential. When Coulson and his team assaulted the Cybertek facility, Mike stayed with Garrett in order to protect him. Coulson arrives, engaging Garrett but is overwhelmed until Nick Fury arrives for support and the two are able to beat Garrett back. When Deathlok learns Skye has rescued Ace, he turns on Garrett, incapacitating him with a rocket and then crushing his skull. In the aftermath Mike, unable to face his son, goes off on his own to redeem himself.

Sometime afterwards Mike was approached by Coulson with an invitation to join S.H.I.E.L.D. Peterson accepted and was sent overseas in pursuit of a HYDRA scientist interested in superhumans named List. However, when Robert Gonzales and his faction of S.H.I.E.L.D. usurps Coulson as director, Peterson was pulled off this assignment. Meeting up with Coulson and Lance Hunter, they steal a Quinjet in order to search for Skye, who had been taken in by the Inhumans.

First the team heads to San Francisco to pick up Leo Fitz, who had left when the new SHIELD regime took control. Next they travelled to Tijuana to recruit Ward and Agent 33. Upon arrival Peterson takes 33 hostage, then Coulson, using her phone, calls Ward for a meeting. When he arrived, Peterson scans him with his x-ray vision, ordering him to removes the concealed knives and guns. While Peterson kept watch, Coulson offered to erase Ward's memories to help him build a new life if he helped them on this mission to infiltrate HYDRA and locate Skye, to which Ward agreed.

Revealing that he had successfully brainwashed Sunil Bakshi, Ward proposed to use him to gain access to the high ranking members of HYDRA. Posing as Bakshi's bodyguard Deathlok attended a meeting between Bakshi and Dr. List, during which Bakshi offered to trade Peterson to List for his experiments, in exchange for a meeting with Baron Wolfgang von Strucker. Peterson readied himself to engage, but was ordered by Coulson to back down and play along. They soon learn that List has been tracking the Inhuman Gordon’s movements and finally pinned him down. List then sends Bakshi, Deathlok and a team of HYDRA soldiers to capture him, along with any other enhanced they find. There Peterson encountered Lincoln Campbell, the two end up fighting and knock each other out. HYDRA then takes the two in to their custody.

Sometime later Peterson awoke in a cell with all his weapons deactivated and Lincoln Campbell in the cell next to him. After a short conversation the pair were gassed and knocked out, ready for experimentation. During the first round of experiments, Dr. List removed his eye and dismantled his cybernetic leg. When he was done Peterson was returned to his cell, where he was found by Phil Coulson's team, including Skye and Jemma Simmons. While Skye went off to save Lincoln Campbell, Simmons stayed and tended to his injuries. After the rescue mission he was taken back to the Playground where he, Fitz and Simmons discussed resorting his cybernetics.

deck: King of Cats is Catwoman's brother. He has romantic feelings towards her. A character who appeared in a golden age Batman story was later established as being an Earth 2 character in a Bronze age Superman story.
description:
History

Gotham City was struck by a series of feline-related crimes, perpetrated not by the now-reformed Selina Kyle, but by a costumed criminal known as The King of Cats, a cunning mastermind whose theme revolves around cats. The King of Cats sends flowers to Kyle, causing Batman to investigate her involvement. He soon becomes convinced that she is innocent, but asks her to aid in arresting the King of Cats. Selina, however, refuses after realizing that the King of Cats was her brother Karl. The King of Cats attempts to lure Selina out of her retirement and back into a life of crime. He is easily captured by Batman and Robin, but Selina pleads with Batman to let him go. When Batman refuses, she knocks him out and allows her brother to escape. Selina asks her brother to end his criminal career and turn himself in, and he promises to consider the offer. Shortly after, Batman attacks the King of Cats at the zoo and in the following battle, both are thrown into separate tiger pens, each trapped without one being able to aid the other. Catwoman, in her old costume, arrives and saves both from certain doom. The King of Cats is remorseful over his crimes, and he promises to abandon his criminal ways and turn himself in.

After several years in prison, Karl was paroled. He remained free on his parole, and was glimpsed in Superman Family #211 walking Selina down the aisle when she wed Bruce Wayne. -This Bronze age appearance firmly establishes the King of Cats as an Earth 2 character.

deck: Princess of the Crystal Empire who was Twilight's foal sitter when she was young and is married to her older brother Shining Armor.
description:
Description:

Princess Mi Amore Cadenza is an Alicorn and the co-ruler of the Crystal Empire together with her husband, Shining Armor. She's one of the five princesses of Equestria and is well-known for being the "Princess of Love", which is a title acquired by helping ponies overcome their problems in that particular area.

Cadence is also Flurry Heart's mother and was the foal-sister of Twilight Sparkle( Currently Cadence is her sister-in-law after marrying Twilight's brother).

Creation/Character Evolution:

Lauren Faust was involved in the creation of the story in which this princess appears for the first time. At this point of development, Cadance wasn't created as an alicorn and Faust herself was surprised to see it as such; The decision was made after she was no longer working on the series. Faust, before that, had decided that Princess Celestia and Princess Luna would be the only alicorns in the series. Like Celestia and Luna, Cadance is initially called a unicorn in the series, despite having both a unicorn horn and pegasus wings and following the term "alicorn" began to be used from the third season onwards, thus is even described as such in the last episode of the fourth season.

History:

Not much is know of Cadence's past, but apparently, she was a pegasus before acquiring Alicorhood.

During her school times, Cadence was a popular pony and admired by many, but still was lovable with every pony around her and always willing to give a hoof to help.

Her first encounter with Shining Armor was actually an accident when she helped him to get up from the ground, which sparkled Shining's love for Cadence at the first moment when saw her.

They both fall in love with each other during the Fall Formal. Princess Cadance appears for the first time during the TV Show in the final episode of the second season of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic. She was the foal-sitter of Twilight Sparkle when she was younger and is currently married to Twilight's brother, Canterlot's Royal Guard, Shining Armor. She was being first mentioned as "Princess Mi Amore Cadenza". She rules the Crystal Empire together with Shining Armor. According to Amy Keating Rogers, Cadance was an orphan Pegasus who was raised by Earth ponies, then Princess Celestia adopts her as his niece. She is also a close friend of Twilight Sparkle and supposedly "a very distant relative" of Princess Amore, the former unicorn ruler of the Crystal Empire.

Cutie Mark:

Cadance's Cutie Mark alternates between two different ones, throughout the episode " A Canterlot Wedding". The cutie mark, a crystal heart, is sometimes represented with a single mirrored facet at its center, and sometimes with multiple facets around its center. Cadance toys use the one-facet version, embedded in a gilded decorated frame. Her cutie mark bears a strong resemblance to the crystal heart of "The Crystal Empire -Part 1 and 2". In The Crystal Empire - Part 2, when she carries the crystal heart, her cutie mark shines as if surrounded by its magic.
